        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"768875\">Joel Pitman</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/How.20to.20def.20term.20in.20lean.2E/near/491348023\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>many thanks to  <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"757121\">Zhang Qinchuan</span>  and <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <br>\nI have another question</p>\n<p><div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Filter</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">Could</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">you</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">explain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">why</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">works?</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀ᶠ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">aesop?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hn</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">linarith</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">but</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">doesn't</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀ᶠ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- aesop?</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hn</span>\n</code></pre></div><br>\n</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Write you question <code>Could you explain ...</code> as comment, just like <code>--aesop?</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Filter</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">--Could you explain why this works?</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">∀ᶠ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">atTop</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">≥</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">aesop?</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Put your cursor at <code>aesop?</code>, there is <code>simp_all only [ge_iff_le, eventually_atTop]\n  sorry</code> at InfoView which simplify your goal to <code>∃ a, ∀ (b : ℕ), a ≤ b → b + 4 ≤ 2 * b</code>.</p>\n<p>Without such simplification, <code>use 4</code> cannot handle <code>∀ᶠ n in atTop, 2 * n ≥ n + 4</code> directly.</p>",
